<div class="page-md">

  <h1 style="margin:0 0 8px;">About Recruiter Rankings</h1>
  <p class="text-muted" style="margin:0 0 40px;">How it works, who it's for, and how we protect your privacy.</p>

  <h2 id="mission">Mission</h2>
  <p>Improve the recruiter–candidate experience by publishing de-identified, standardized quality signals with a safe right-of-reply.</p>

  <h2 id="who-its-for">Who it's for</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Candidates</strong> — Sign in with Clerk (email or social), submit reviews anonymously, browse aggregates without logging in.</li>
    <li><strong>Recruiters</strong> — Claim your LinkedIn profile, exercise right-of-reply before reviews go public, manage your public record.</li>
    <li><strong>Hiring companies</strong> — View aggregate quality signals for your recruiting partners. B2B benchmarks coming in GA.</li>
    <li><strong>Moderators &amp; Admins</strong> — Review submission queue, handle takedown requests, manage identity verifications.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="how-reviews-work">How reviews work</h2>
  <ol>
    <li>Sign in with Clerk (email or LinkedIn required for submission).</li>
    <li>Submit a review: 8 quality dimensions scored 1–5, plus an overall score and optional free-text experience.</li>
    <li>Review enters the moderation queue; moderators approve, flag, or remove within the SLA.</li>
    <li>Approved reviews are added to the recruiter's aggregate.</li>
    <li>Recruiter profile becomes publicly visible once the k-anonymity threshold is met (≥ 5 approved reviews).</li>
  </ol>

  <h2 id="quality-dimensions">Quality dimensions (1–5)</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Responsiveness</li>
    <li>Role clarity</li>
    <li>Understanding candidate needs</li>
    <li>Fairness &amp; inclusivity</li>
    <li>Timeline management</li>
    <li>Feedback quality</li>
    <li>Professionalism &amp; respect</li>
    <li>Job / role match quality</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="authentication-identity">Authentication &amp; identity</h2>
  <p>Authentication is managed by <a href="https://clerk.com">Clerk</a> (email, LinkedIn, GitHub).</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Review submission</strong> — requires a verified email address or LinkedIn account.</li>
    <li><strong>Recruiter profile claiming</strong> — requires a LinkedIn profile challenge: a one-time 128-bit token placed publicly in your LinkedIn profile, TTL 7 days, stored as hash only (never plaintext).</li>
    <li><strong>Moderators &amp; Admins</strong> — require email + LinkedIn + GitHub + 2FA via Clerk.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="data-privacy">Data &amp; privacy</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Only aggregated signals are publicly visible — no individual review text is surfaced.</li>
    <li>Company names are bucketed by size (e.g., &lt; 50 employees shown as "Small company") to reduce re-identification risk.</li>
    <li>Email addresses are stored as an HMAC hash for deduplication; the raw email is envelope-encrypted at rest.</li>
    <li>PII retention: 180 days. Abuse metadata: 30 days.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="roadmap">Roadmap</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>✓ <strong>POC</strong> — Core models, review submission, identity verification, moderation queue, public recruiter directory.</li>
    <li><strong>Beta</strong> — Full right-of-reply UI, profile claiming, suppression thresholds, B2B company dashboard skeleton.</li>
    <li><strong>GA</strong> — Expanded compliance, regional data isolation, pricing/payments, hardened anti-abuse.</li>
  </ul>

</div>
